William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
Your obituary of William Woodruff (died September 25) states that "in 1946 he had resumed his studies in economic history in Oxford, and became a member of Houblon-Norma research in 1950, while he was doing a BSc, an MA and a PhD".
